{"type":"message","id":"f71d0d66","parentId":"f9e7f959","timestamp":"2026-04-06T06:08:06.856Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ah! The OLD backup uses 3103 for BOTH:1. proxyPort: 3103 (where ws-proxy listens for clients)\n2. gatewayWsUrl: ws://localhost:3103 (where ws-proxy connects to Gateway)\n\nBut wait - that's the same port! How does that work? That's the conflict I'm seeing.Actually wait - it says \"WebSocket proxy listening on ${CONFIG.proxyPort} -> ${CONFIG.gatewayWsUrl}\". So it WAS configured to listen on 3103 and also connect to 3103. So how did it work before?Oh, I think I now understand! The way it could work is:1. Gateway binds to 127.0.0.1:3103 (localhost only)2. ws-proxy tried to bind to 0.0.0.0:3103 - but this would fail if Gateway is already there!Unless... they were NOT running at the same time? Or perhaps Gateway wasn't running when ws-proxy started?Wait, looking at my earlier grep output for the running processes:- PID 4338 was ws-proxy (running since 12:15)\n- PID 5524 is openclaw-gateway (running since... let me check)But actually, let me check when Gateway started - if it was AFTER ws-proxy then there WAS a conflict. Let me check the start times:\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"019d61673a7001e1507ce87a6626ba65","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查进程启动时间\nps -eo pid,lstart,cmd | grep -E \"ws-proxy|openclaw-gatewa\" | grep -v grep"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":3204,"output":334,"cacheRead":30848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34386,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775455670552,"responseId":"019d616702e847283b6c18b184369228"}}
