{"type":"message","id":"cf3440ab","parentId":"4c7c0204","timestamp":"2026-04-06T06:08:34.277Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so:- Gateway started at 13:13:56- Old ws-proxy (PID 4338) was running since 12:15 (before Gateway!)\n\nSo the old ws-proxy started at 12:15, then Gateway started at 13:13. This created a conflict at 13:13 when Gateway tried to bind to 3103!But wait - if Gateway started at 13:13 and took over 3103, then the old ws-proxy (PID 4338) should have crashed or failed. Let me verify:Actually, the issue might be that Gateway binds to 127.0.0.1:3103 (localhost), while ws-proxy tried to bind to 0.0.0.0:3103 (any). In some cases this could work... or maybe there's something else going on.Let me just try a different approach: use a different port for ws-proxy to listen on, like 3105, and keep Gateway at 3103.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n明白了！问题是：\n- Gateway (pid 5524) 从 13:13 开始占用 3103 端口\n- ws-proxy 也想用 3103，但绑定冲突\n\n**解决方案**：让 ws-proxy 用不同端口（比如 3105），Gateway 保持在 3103。\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"019d616770dc715e671ec9f89c1c5cd3","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":" proxyPort: parseInt(process.env.PROXY_WS_PORT || '3105', 10),","oldText":" proxyPort: parseInt(process.env.PROXY_WS_PORT || '3103', 10),"}],"path":"/home/ai/openclaw-router/ws-proxy.js"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":1795,"output":360,"cacheRead":32768,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34923,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775455686892,"responseId":"019d616713fbd742c93ece708c72f827"}}
